\begin{document}

\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=0.5cm]
    \foreach \i in {1,...,6}{\node (n\i) at (\i,0) {$1$};}
    \node (n7) at (7,0) {$7$};
\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

### Linear Realization for \(\{1^7, 7^{17}, 8^3\}\)

```latex
\documentclass[tikz,border=2mm]{standalone}
\begin{document}

\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=0.5cm]
    \foreach \i in {1,...,7}{\node (n\i) at (\i,0) {$1$};}
    \foreach \i in {1,...,17}{\node (n18\i) at (\i+7,0) {$7$};}
    \foreach \i in {1,...,3}{\node (n19\i) at (\i+34,0) {$8$};}
\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- In the first realization, we have six nodes labeled "1" followed by one node labeled "7".
- In the second realization, we have seven nodes labeled "1", followed by seventeen nodes labeled "7", and finally three nodes labeled "8".

